pageTitle: Hoyer: Today We Must Finish Our Work and Take Action on a Comprehensive Aid Package | The Office of Democratic Whip Steny Hoyer
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {6721=“Congress appropriated $62.3 billion in emergency relief less than two weeks after Hurricane Katrina struck New Orleans and the Gulf Coast in 2005. I voted for that. That was the right thing to do. As it was then, it is now - the right thing to do. There's no reason why the people of New York, New Jersey, and affected areas should have to wait any longer. This is a bipartisan effort.}
